---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Granny Flats Mornington | Sea-Change & Short-Stay Market | (03) 9003 0108"
  description="Granny flat builders for Mornington — sea-change demographic, holiday-home market, Peninsula Shire short-stay registration rules, coastal salt-zone build spec. Free design consultation."
  canonical="https://frankstongrannyflats.com.au/mornington/">
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">Mornington &middot; Mt Martha &middot; Mornington Park</span>
      <h1>Granny flats in <span class="accent">Mornington</span>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Mornington is a beach town with two distinct granny flat markets &mdash; permanent
        residents wanting a second dwelling for family, and sea-change owners looking
        at the short-stay rental potential. The Peninsula Shire short-stay registration
        rules changed in 2023; we&rsquo;ll walk you through what&rsquo;s possible.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book a free consultation</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">Why Mornington</span>
      <h2>The Mornington granny flat story.</h2>
      <div class="divider"></div>

      <div style="max-width: 65rem;">
        <h3>The short-stay registration question.</h3>
        <p>
          Mornington Peninsula Shire introduced <strong>short-stay accommodation
          registration</strong> in 2023. Both the primary dwelling and any second
          dwelling used for short-stay (Airbnb, Stayz, similar) must be registered,
          and the Shire has precinct-specific caps to manage neighbourhood impact.
          Some streets are at or near the cap. We check the precinct status before
          you commit to a build that depends on short-stay returns.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Design for permanent and short-stay flexibility.</h3>
        <p>
          The smart move on Mornington blocks is to design for both uses simultaneously:
          one bedroom (works for couples or solo travellers), private entry from a
          side path, separate parking on a paved bay, lockable from the main house
          but with optional internal access. That way it works as family
          accommodation 9 months a year and Airbnb in summer, or vice versa, or you
          can switch entirely if regulations change.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Block sizes and DDO context.</h3>
        <p>
          Mornington blocks range widely &mdash; 400m&sup2; near the village/beachfront,
          800&ndash;1,200m&sup2; on the inland side toward Mornington Park, 1,500m&sup2;+
          on the Mt Martha border. The DDO (Design and Development Overlay) applies
          across most of the residential zone with specific height limits near the
          ridgeline view corridors. We site-survey before quoting on any Mornington
          block &mdash; what works on Esplanade Drive doesn&rsquo;t necessarily fly
          one street back.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Typical Mornington jobs.</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>1-bedroom modular granny flat with separate entry + parking, $130K&ndash;$180K, designed for dual-use</li>
          <li>Mornington Park heritage-area rear cottage, custom on-site, $200K&ndash;$260K</li>
          <li>Bayview-compliant 2-bedroom on Mornington Hill (height controls), $200K&ndash;$280K</li>
          <li>Short-stay-registered second dwelling with full Shire compliance package</li>
          <li>SDA-compliant build for ageing parent + carer (NDIS Improved Liveability)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Other service areas.</h2>
      <div class="areas-grid">
        <a class="area-pill" href="/frankston-south/">Frankston South</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/mt-eliza/">Mt Eliza</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/carrum-downs/">Carrum Downs</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/seaford/">Seaford</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/mornington-peninsula/">Mornington Peninsula</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="cta-block">
        <h2>Free Mornington design consultation.</h2>
        <p>Short-stay rules navigated. Coastal spec by default. Fixed quote in 7 days.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;">
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book online</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
